# Permanent Design Decisions — Do Not Revert

These rules must **NEVER** be changed without explicit instruction from the user.

## Profile Photo

- The circular profile photo border/ring is always **WHITE** — never blue, never gray
- The camera icon on the profile photo is always positioned **INSIDE** the white ring, overlapping the bottom of the photo
- The camera icon style matches the cover photo camera icon (dark rounded square, white icon)

## Header

- "Switch to Worker", "Switch to Client", "Become a Star" text is always **BLACK (#222)** — never blue, never underlined
- These links show a **pill-shaped hover state in #ebebeb** — no other hover style

## Brand Colors

- Primary brand color: **#1B4FBA** (blue) — used for buttons, links, active states only
- **Never** apply #1B4FBA to plain text links in the header

## Worker Card

- Worker preview card on the service area page aligns to the **TOP** of the map — never centered

## Footer

- Footer always contains: **Privacy Policy | Terms of Service | © 2025 Star**
- Footer is present on **every** page

## General

- Never remove features or UI elements that are already working without explicit instruction
- Never revert a visual fix that was explicitly requested
- When in doubt about a style decision, **check this file first** before applying defaults

## Before committing

Any time a task touches files that contain these elements, **re-read this file** and verify none of these rules are violated before committing.
